abstract: Economists at the bank think the president has a “narrow” advantage over Democratic challengers in his re-election bid.
snippet: Economists at the bank think the president has a “narrow” advantage over Democratic challengers in his re-election bid.
lead_paragraph: Good Monday morning. ICYMI: Tiger Woods wasn’t the only winner from the Masters yesterday. So was Nike — which turned out this ad within minutes of his victory. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

abstract: Mr. Trump’s haul is about the size of what Senators Bernie Sanders and Kamala Harris — the top two Democratic fund-raisers — raised combined in the first quarter.
snippet: Mr. Trump’s haul is about the size of what Senators Bernie Sanders and Kamala Harris — the top two Democratic fund-raisers — raised combined in the first quarter.
lead_paragraph: President Trump raised more than $30 million for his re-election in the first three months of 2019 and now sits atop more than $40 million, his campaign said on Sunday.

snippet: Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s request, which came after President Trump tweeted a video attacking Ms. Omar using images of 9/11, was not based on new threats, an aide said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi asked House officials on Sunday to review security measures intended to protect Representative Ilhan Omar after President Trump tweeted a video attacking the Minnesota Democrat using images of the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks.

abstract: The question of how — and when — to engage with Mr. Trump’s political broadsides has become a dividing line among Democrats and party activists.

abstract: The total for Ms. Gillibrand, announced after many rivals disclosed their numbers, trails the amounts raised by the other five senators currently running for president.
snippet: The total for Ms. Gillibrand, announced after many rivals disclosed their numbers, trails the amounts raised by the other five senators currently running for president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Kirsten Gillibrand’s presidential campaign raised $3 million in the first quarter of the year, a spokeswoman said on Sunday, a disappointing sum that ranked her last among the six senators currently running for president.

headline_main: 2020 Presidential Candidates’ Tax Returns So Far
byline_original: By Thomas Kaplan, K.K. Rebecca Lai, Jasmine C. Lee and Denise Lu

abstract: In his writings as a student and young politician, he fixated on the kind of media narratives that have propelled his 2020 campaign.
snippet: In his writings as a student and young politician, he fixated on the kind of media narratives that have propelled his 2020 campaign.
lead_paragraph: The question was simple enough, but Senator John Edwards squirmed painfully. For 49 long seconds, the North Carolina Democrat, a masterful courtroom orator, sputtered before a crowd at Harvard, unable to settle on a favorite movie.

abstract: The tone of a lawmaker’s letter suggested Democrats are prepared to take their request to court, initiating what could be a protracted legal fight over Congress’s oversight powers.
snippet: The tone of a lawmaker’s letter suggested Democrats are prepared to take their request to court, initiating what could be a protracted legal fight over Congress’s oversight powers.
lead_paragraph: A Democratic House chairman on Saturday castigated the Treasury Department for failing to meet his deadline to furnish President Trump’s tax returns, arguing that the administration’s apparent concerns over his use of powers outlined in the Internal Revenue Service’s tax code “lack merit.”
